TY  - JOUR
T1  - Organization Development: A Political Perspective
AU  - Cobb, Anthony T.
AU  - Margulies, Newton
Y1  - 1981/01/01
PY  - 1981
DA  - 1981/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1981.4287998
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1981.4287998
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 49
EP  - 59
VL  - 6
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - It is now accepted that organizational politics exist in every organization and are involved in almost every facet of organizational life. Organizational politics are certainly involved in intervention programs. Despite these facts, organization development (OD) has been characterized as lacking any political sophistication whatsoever. In order to increase their success rate, OD consultants have been asked to become more politically involved in their intervention programs [Bennis, 1969; Pettigrew, 1975]. We argue here that OD has developed an unrecognized political orientation that aids OD consultants in the political arena and supports their intervention programs, and we explore the practical and ethical/value considerations of greater political involvement.
AB  - It is now accepted that organizational politics exist in every organization and are involved in almost every facet of organizational life. Organizational politics are certainly involved in intervention programs. Despite these facts, organization development (OD) has been characterized as lacking any political sophistication whatsoever. In order to increase their success rate, OD consultants have been asked to become more politically involved in their intervention programs [Bennis, 1969; Pettigrew, 1975]. We argue here that OD has developed an unrecognized political orientation that aids OD consultants in the political arena and supports their intervention programs, and we explore the practical and ethical/value considerations of greater political involvement.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1981.4287998
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.1981.4287998
Y2  - 2026/04/24
ER  - 

